text: Kameyevo () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative center of Kameyevsky Selsoviet, Mishkinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 693 as of 2010. There are 15 streets. == Geography == It is located 12 km from Mishkino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mishkinsky District
title: Kameyevo
